37:08.017 --> 37:09.894
<i>to see how it's gonna hold up.</i>

37:09.894 --> 37:13.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:13.565 --> 37:15.066
It goes right through it.

37:15.066 --> 37:16.735
I'd kind of like
to keep it around.

37:16.735 --> 37:18.528
I think it'd be
real handy around here.

37:18.528 --> 37:22.490
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:22.490 --> 37:24.784
- Mike, Alex, welcome back
to the Forge.

37:24.784 --> 37:26.703
You've had five days
at your home forges to work

37:26.703 --> 37:28.371
on your horseman's axes.

37:28.371 --> 37:30.832
Mike, tell us about your weapon.

37:30.832 --> 37:32.876
- It's a little rough
around the edges,

37:32.876 --> 37:34.669
but I think
it will perform well.

37:34.669 --> 37:36.755
<i>And I can't wait</i>
<i>to see it happen.</i>

37:36.755 --> 37:38.506
<i>- Alex?</i>

37:38.506 --> 37:40.675
- Everything just fell
into place for me,

37:40.675 --> 37:42.677
<i>even though I had to make</i>
<i>some last-minute changes.</i>

37:42.677 --> 37:44.387
<i>And I'm looking forward</i>
<i>to seeing it tear apart</i>

37:44.387 --> 37:46.389
some ballistics dummies.

37:46.389 --> 37:49.309
- All right, gentlemen.
Up first, the kill test.

37:49.309 --> 37:51.728
Doug?

37:51.728 --> 37:54.314
- The horseman's axe, it's
actually two weapons in one.

37:54.314 --> 37:56.399
It's got an edge
that an lacerate and chop,

37:56.399 --> 37:59.694
and a spike that can penetrate
and crush bones.

37:59.694 --> 38:02.489
To see what kind of lethal
damage your axe will do,

38:02.489 --> 38:04.199
I will take your horseman's axe

38:04.199 --> 38:06.910
and deliver lethal blows
on this ballistics dummy.

38:06.910 --> 38:08.203
Mike, you're up first.
You ready?

38:08.203 --> 38:09.954
- Yes, I am.
- As you can see,

38:09.954 --> 38:11.915
I'm recovering from an injury.

38:11.915 --> 38:14.000
So one of my students
will have the satisfaction

38:14.000 --> 38:16.169
of testing your weapon.

38:16.169 --> 38:23.134
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:29.307 --> 38:32.685
[indistinct conversation]

38:32.685 --> 38:34.479
Well, Mike, let's talk
about your weapon.

38:34.479 --> 38:37.148
Your edge over here is sharp.

38:37.148 --> 38:40.527
It lacerated
deep into the bowels right here.

38:40.527 --> 38:43.571
Your spike definitely caved in
all the way through the chest

38:43.571 --> 38:45.281
and straight into the heart.

38:45.281 --> 38:47.367
The only issue we have
is that your handle

38:47.367 --> 38:49.160
is a little bit
on the rounded side.

38:49.160 --> 38:51.204
So there is a tendency
to slightly roll.

38:51.204 --> 38:53.873
But overall,
your weapon will kill.

38:53.873 --> 38:55.333
- Thank you.

38:55.333 --> 38:57.377
- Alex, you're up next.
You ready?

38:57.377 --> 38:58.962
- Yes.
- Let's do this.

38:58.962 --> 39:00.463
- All right.

39:00.463 --> 39:02.090
I'm pretty proud
of what I created.

39:02.090 --> 39:03.925
It's just a little heavy,

39:03.925 --> 39:06.636
<i>and that's a bit</i>
<i>of a concern going in.</i>

39:06.636 --> 39:13.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:14.936 --> 39:16.646
Sweet.
[chuckles]

39:16.646 --> 39:19.816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:19.816 --> 39:24.237
- Alex. Your weapon here is
a little bit on the heavy side.

39:24.237 --> 39:26.781
But you know what?
It is well balanced.

39:26.781 --> 39:30.493
The edge of your blade here
cut deep in the chest cavity

39:30.493 --> 39:32.036
and it broke the bones.

39:32.036 --> 39:33.955
Your spike here--
right into the heart.

39:33.955 --> 39:35.832
And, of course,
on the swing,

39:35.832 --> 39:39.419
it pretty much has disemboweled
the dummy right there.

39:39.419 --> 39:42.380
Your weapon will kill.

39:42.380 --> 39:43.965
- Yes. Thank you.

39:43.965 --> 39:46.718
- Next up is
the strength test. J.?

39:46.718 --> 39:48.720
- Now, we know ice can be
very brutal on an edge.

39:48.720 --> 39:50.597
So I'm going to take
your horseman's axes

39:50.597 --> 39:52.640
and repeatedly strike them
into these large blocks of ice

39:52.640 --> 39:54.058
to see how well they hold up.

39:54.058 --> 39:55.310
Mike, you're up first.
You ready?

39:55.310 --> 39:57.812
- Yes, I am.

39:57.812 --> 40:00.440
<i>I think Alex has the advantage</i>
<i>at this time,</i>

40:00.440 --> 40:02.817
so going
into the ice block test,

40:02.817 --> 40:05.987
I'm concerned there may be
a fail point in the head,

40:05.987 --> 40:07.906
handle area.

40:07.906 --> 40:10.408
<i>But this is it. Very nervous.</i>

40:10.408 --> 40:13.453
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:15.512 --> 40:17.264
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:17.264 --> 40:19.140
<i>- Going into</i>
<i>the ice block test,</i>

40:19.140 --> 40:21.685
<i>I'm concerned there</i>
<i>may be a fail point</i>

40:21.685 --> 40:23.144
in the head, handle area.

40:23.144 --> 40:30.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:42.789 --> 40:48.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:48.628 --> 40:50.714
- [groans]

40:50.714 --> 40:52.382
- Well, Mike,
unfortunately,

40:52.382 --> 40:54.676
we had a serious failure
on your axe..

40:54.676 --> 40:57.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:57.512 --> 41:01.892
With this weld point and
the junction of the belt hook.

41:01.892 --> 41:04.477
Now, Alex, you still have to
pass this test.

41:04.477 --> 41:07.355
Are you ready?
- Yes, I'm ready.

41:07.355 --> 41:12.068
There's only one thing standing
between me and a $10,000 check,

41:12.068 --> 41:14.696
and it's really big,
and it's made of ice.

41:14.696 --> 41:21.661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:35.467 --> 41:39.012
- Now, Alex, your horseman's axe
did quite a job on that ice.

41:39.012 --> 41:42.182
Everything's still tight, and
your edge is still razor-sharp.

41:42.182 --> 41:43.683
- Thank you.

41:43.683 --> 41:47.103
- So, all in all,
very nicely done.

41:47.103 --> 41:49.481
- Bladesmiths, our weapons tests
here are designed

41:49.481 --> 41:51.483
to be exceptionally brutal

41:51.483 --> 41:54.110
in order to set your weapons
apart from one another.

41:54.110 --> 41:57.530
Mike, your blade did not
survive our strength test.

41:57.530 --> 42:00.283
For that reason, I have to ask
you to please leave the Forge.

42:00.283 --> 42:02.202
- Okay.

42:02.202 --> 42:04.079
<i>I am disappointed,</i>
<i>but when I go home,</i>

42:04.079 --> 42:06.665
I'm gonna have a smile
on my face.

42:06.665 --> 42:10.502
<i>"Forged in Fire" has risen me</i>
<i>from the dead somehow.</i>

42:10.502 --> 42:13.713
I will take this forward with me
for the rest of my life.

42:13.713 --> 42:16.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:16.007 --> 42:18.885
- Alex, congratulations. You are
the "Forged in Fire" champion

42:18.885 --> 42:21.054
and will be receiving
a check for $10,000.

42:21.054 --> 42:23.390
Good job.
[applause]

42:23.390 --> 42:26.017
- Thank--Whew.

42:26.017 --> 42:27.727
It's surreal.
It's really surreal.

42:27.727 --> 42:28.853
- Well, come on over here
and shake our hands.

42:28.853 --> 42:30.647
- Oh, wow.

42:30.647 --> 42:32.399
<i>I can't really fathom</i>
<i>that I won.</i>

42:32.399 --> 42:34.693
Like, I won.

42:34.693 --> 42:37.195
<i>Definitely tops everything else</i>
<i>I've ever done.</i>

42:37.195 --> 42:39.364
Being the "Forged in Fire"
champion

42:39.364 --> 42:41.116
<i>just shows I've applied</i>

42:41.116 --> 42:42.909
<i>what I've always tried</i>
<i>to teach others.</i>

42:42.909 --> 42:44.995
Never stop learning.

